ėíŔ@fb4f19f5a75148449c5639a25c1ec05c6c4eb3a3bfc649d3cfceca30ae61dc6cŕěTitle: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Nushell 0.26
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.26 of Nu. It's a polish release with lots of improvements.
íŔ@54a2858658792a60d117895d1b184bd546fb3e7cf247aab8d6125df732782b43ŕTitle: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.26 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.26.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want all the goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=extra``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
íŔ@cfb18b26742347a08f1aa41099cbb4837b5a03c05f039d02b4e928d26b92a49fŕKTitle: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Rest support in custom commands (LhKipp, sophiajt)
Content:
You can now refer to a rest argument in your custom command:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
def my-cmd[...rest:int] {
    echo $rest | math sum
}

```
Elements of the rest are referred to with positions, like 
``$rest.1``
 for the 2nd position.
íŔ@98dc43aa8426eeaafc9edae7a47a28c461940d9f68ee93de0d1cb2f013df35b4ŔųTitle: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Short flags in custom commands (LhKipp)
Content:
You can now also added an optional shorthand flag to longhand flags:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
def foo [--bar(-b): int] {
    echo $bar
}

foo -b 10
foo --bar 10

```
íŔ@9fe3463a72ca44e6ab0cc458f89e7b9377d546414063948b32fb9b034fcac81eŕ7Title: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Improved build times (sophiajt, stormasm)
Content:
When building from scratch, you may now notice that Nushell builds slightly faster. This comes from refactoring large crates into smaller crates and replacing some of our support crates with similar crates that compile faster.
íŔ@29b56295ed8f815c5460e07dea5f8970be6f0ffd9e7c7db0ce4ab40b669a3acfŕWTitle: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Improvements
Content:
I hope you like improvements. We got a 
lot
 of them this release.
fdcnred added support for using 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2973] multi-byte chars as padding
, improved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2955] ansi and char support
, improved the output of 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2959] ``sys``
, optimized some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2937] regex usage
, removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2924] ``set``
 from Windows built-ins
, added support for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2906] comparing a string and a filepath
JosephTLyons removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2970] unnecessary clones
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2969] fixed some test macros
andrasio added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2965] column path support to many 
``str``
 commands
sophiajt added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2964] error checking for bad rows in column paths
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2952] proper flushing of stdout
, split 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2898] nu-cli and nu-engine
, treat 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2890] the startup commands a single script
 which improves startup times, fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2893] reading/writing of bigint/bigdecimal
baoyachi updated 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2963] shadow-rs support
, removed some of the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2935] git support that was no longer needed
kubouch added the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2953] --skip flag to 
``nth``
ahkrr fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2951] variable scopes for 
``def``
 parameters
brightly-salty 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2949] replaces the dirs/directories supporting crates
jankeronmes fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2948] Gitpod tests
LhKipp fixed a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2945] parser bug that prevented invocations and ranges from being parsed correctly
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2939] ``def``
 documentation
, updated 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2925] ``alias``
 docs
DivineGod moved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2927] keybinding_path to nu-data
Gymea fixed the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2924] dirs dependency in nu-engine
, improved the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2915] ``help``
 logic when the command does not have a description
, fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2894] ``which``
 output for aliases
gillespiecd added the support for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2913] reverse ranges
stormasm refactored 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2910] nu-cli and split off commands into nu-command
TrevorAC99 fixed a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2880] rust-embed build breakage
íŔ@6c317bc2796d861cc0ca39b2885a52f32feb30e87143b888fb25fa9d0acd21fcŕsTitle: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Breaking changes
Content:
``ps``
 and 
``sys``
 are now served using a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2954] different supporting crate
. The functionality difference between the old crate and the new crate may mean a lack of fields that existed before, or different values than before (as it may be calculated differently).
We removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2940] ``str set``
. This command was one of the first of its style and has since been replaced by more general commands like 
``update``
.
Internal architecture: the Primitive case for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2887] lines has been removed
. Instead, use strings.
Internal architecture: the Path and Pattern primitives are now called 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2889] FilePath and GlobPattern
 respectively.
íŔ@03ef966d1b3d1cc46ab3941d2482ec9652330063e53f8733425c0deef770a909ŕ=Title: title: Nushell 0.26
Path: Looking forward
Content:
We've been humbled by the feedback we got on the 0.25 release and appreciate the support. Looking forward, we'll be continuing to polish the features that landed in 0.25 as we prepare for using these features in larger scripts and in custom completion logic.
